<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-11-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="807" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d807">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-02"><hi rend="italic">November 2,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Eddy reports the situation improving. The general strike will come
                            to an end to-morrow. It is hoped that railway communication will be open
                            within a few days. Small disturbances continue and the revolutionary
                            party is still active. The situation in Finland is serious.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>